description:
HUB International Limited (“HUB”) is the 5th largest global insurance and employee benefits broker, providing a broad array of property, casualty, risk management, life and health, employee benefits, investment and wealth management products and services. With over 18,000 employees in 750 offices throughout North America and Canada, HUB has grown substantially, in part due to our industry leading success in mergers and acquisitions.


We are seeking a highly motivated insurance professional with a college degree, or relevant work experience, and a minimum of three years’ experience in insurance. The position includes working from the Client’s office a minimum of three days per week or as directed by Client and HUB.


Responsible for day-to-day management and maintenance of all policies-Client’s office:

* Issue COI and EPI (evidence of property), timely;
* Provide COIs and related information to requesting parties as needed and approved by Client;
* Review invoices and submit for approval and payment from Client;
* Label and save policies, endorsements, renewal info, and invoices on Client’s server;
* Gather information from Client -Provide underwriting information for renewals and new business placement:
	+ Applications.
	+ Update/maintain Schedule of Locations & Values.
	+ Update/maintain mortgagee schedule.
	+ Premium allocations.
	+ Financing agreements-oversee timely payment.
	+ Track all payments.
* Property Damage claims – Obtain report and claims information from Client, and report to HUB, track status, coordinate & support process with Property Management/Client. All other claims- reporting of claims will be handled by the client.


Day-to-day responsibilities-Insurance program placed by Property Managers:

* Obtain COI and EPI from Risk Manager (RM);
* Obtain invoices, if needed from RM;
* Review Mortgagee schedule with Client and provide information to RM;
* Follow up for changes, and update the Client’s server;
* Property damage claims- help client with reporting and or information


Other requirements:

* Ordering loss runs, if necessary, for HUB’s use;
* Ability to put together a loss summary;
* Process endorsements, when necessary;
* Process invoices, when necessary;
* Maintain documents in EPIC when appropriate unless it is for Client use only;
* Advanced Excel skills-Must be able to create complex spreadsheets- tables, graphs, calculations, efficiently process large quantities of data.
* Communicate with department manager and Senior Account Executive;
* Comply with HUB’s policies, procedures and privacy guidelines;
* Comply with Client’s policies, procedures and privacy guidelines;


The expected pay range for this position is $80,000 to $90,000 and will be impacted by factors such as the successful candidate’s skills, experience, and work location, as well as the specific position’s business line, scope, and level. HUB International is proud to offer comprehensive benefit and total compensation packages which could include health/dental/vision/life/disability insurance, FSA, HSA and 401(k) accounts, paid-time-off benefits, and commissions for some positions.


Department Account Management & Service
Required Experience: 2-5 years of relevant experience
Required Travel: Negligible
Required Education: Bachelor's degree (4-year degree)
